{
  "stem": "22652.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and I was told later on-- I mean, were talking 50 years later-- one of the nuns, whose name was Deniz Pola Aguanish, she said-- I just found out 50 years later-- she said she took us to the railway station in Paris, and she was in charge of putting children in safe hiding places.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in the train, there were two social workers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, if my recollections are correct, one was Colette and the other one was Ethel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they told us-- now, again, this is from what I remember.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were two social workers, very young girls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One said she was 16, and the other one was 18.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they told us that they were Jewish, but they had a baptismal certificate, and they passed as Catholics.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that we must never tell anyone that we're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- [CRYING] --they were going to put us in a safe place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we would do whatever we were told to do, and what all the other children did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We would participate in all activities, and that they would keep in touch with us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that they would write and come and visit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They kept their words.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we stayed a few days in the convent of Notre Dame de Sion of Grenoble, and then we were put in the convent of Les Soeurs du Bon Pasteur, The Sisters of the Good Shepherd.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was-- it was-- what do you call that?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The nuns don't go out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a cloister.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The nuns all wore white, and they were-- so that's where we were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we stayed there till the eve of the liberation of Grenoble.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Describe a day in, in, in the convent, in the-- in the one that you stayed for the duration?",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
